                        INHERITANCE

----> One class want to use properties of another class, then uses INHERITANCE.
---->  ':' is symbol of inheritance.
----> In inheritance, child class can use self class properties as well as parent class properties.
----> In inheritance, parent class reference variable can uses self class object as well as child class object.


----> Child class only inheriates protected and public property it never inheriates private properties.


TYPES OF INHERITANCE
1)SINGLE LEVEL INHERITANCE:
    One class inheriates only one class at a time.
    e.g:
    class A
    {

    };
    class B: public a
    {

    };
            A -----> B


2) MULTILEVEL INHERITANCE:
    One class inheriates one class at a time, but inheriates multiclass properties at a time.

    one parent class have a only child class.

            A ----> B ----> C ----> D


3)HIRARCHICLE INHERITANCE:
    One class inheriates one class ar a tine, but inheritance multiclass properties at a time.
    One parent class have a multiple child class.
